The paper deals with image classification using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The authors also discuss the importance of domain adaptation, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves data set bias, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM). The use of deep learning models for classification also falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the authors discuss the effect of image quality on classification performance, which is a topic in computer graphics (cs.CR).
